The paper discusses machine learning algorithms that use hyperboxes as fundamental representational and building blocks. This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on learning algorithms and their applications. The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as hyperbox-based models are a type of AI algorithm. The third likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper discusses fuzzy min-max neural networks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper mentions the potential for online adaptation of predictors to streaming data. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.DM (Data Mining), as the paper discusses discovering new information and knowledge from different data sources.
